name: Lamborghini Urus
description: Lamborghini Urus is the first Super Sport Utility Vehicle in the world to merge the soul of a super sports car with the functionality of an SUV.

name: BMW X7
description: The 2022 BMW X7 is a seven-passenger three-row SUV that is available in two trim levels: xDrive40i and M50i.

name: Audi RS7 Sportback
description: The new Audi RS 7 Sportback marks the model's second generation and is more unique than ever before.

name: Ferrari 812 Superfast

name: Bugatti Bolide
description: Bugatti announced the Bolide would be the last car ever made with their W16 engine.

name: Porsche Cayenne
description: The Porsche Cayenne is a series of mid-size luxury crossover sport utility vehicles manufactured by the German automaker Porsche since 2002.

name: Mazda CX 9
description: The Mazda CX-9 is a three-row SUV with seven seats. A six-seat layout is optional, and it swaps the second-row bench seat for a pair of captain's chairs.

name: Mercedes C-Class Cabriolet
description: Powering it is an all-new M264 petrol engine which is compliant to the BS-VI standards.
